commitResults.messageTitle: Level 0. Renamed Duke to Friday, Implemented initial greeting and exit skeletal message.
Level 1. Implemented logic for accepting and echoing inputs of the user as well as exiting once exit flag has been triggered by the user
Level 2. Implemented ability to log user input and displaying them back to the user when requested
Level 3. Mark as Done. Implemented Task class and refactored code to utilize OOP concepts and modularized code for improved readability
Level 4. Added support for tracking ToDos, Deadlines, and Events, refactored code for improved readability, and added comments to easily identify and prevent regression
Updated TextUiTesting using I/O redirection technique with expected inputs and outputs from previous levels to ensure that code does not suffer from regression bugs
Level 5. Implemented Error Handling, Phased out legacy Level 2 for Level 4 implementation of Task list, Added 'help' for list of commands.
Level 6. Implemented Delete functionality with appropriate error handling, included in list of commands
Refactor: Utilise enums for command handling
Update: Implement auto-save and load functionality for tasks
commitResults.messageBody:
The application does not currently persist tasks between sessions, leading
to a loss of data when the application is closed.

Persisting tasks to the hard disk ensures that the user's data is saved
automatically whenever the task list changes, enhancing the user
experience.

This commit introduces the following changes:
* Implement saving tasks to the hard disk whenever the task list changes.
* Load tasks from the hard disk when the chatbot starts up.
* Hardcode the file path as ./data/friday.txt.
* Update .gitignore to exclude the constantly updating ./data/friday.txt.

The file path is hardcoded to simplify the implementation, and the
.gitignore update prevents unnecessary tracking of the data file.
